<!--
  bc-aws-cloudtrail.xml — Custom Wazuh rules for AWS CloudTrail telemetry.

  Rule ID range: 100300-100399 (reserved for bc-aws)
  Telemetry source: wodle aws-s3 module on the Wazuh manager, reading the
                    bc-cloudtrail-logs-997916278486 S3 bucket. Decoded by the
                    built-in Wazuh "aws" decoder.

  Deployed to: /var/ossec/etc/rules/bc-aws-cloudtrail.xml on the manager
               by phase3-install-wazuh.sh via S3 sync on instance boot.

  SOAR contract: Rule IDs 100300-100303 are stable identifiers — Splunk SOAR
  playbooks key on these IDs. Do NOT renumber existing rules.

  >>> FIELD PREFIX (verified 2026-06-02 against the live indexer) <<<
    The aws-s3 wodle decoder nests ALL CloudTrail fields under "aws." — the
    built-in Wazuh amazon ruleset matches e.g. <field name="aws.eventName">.
    Rules MUST use the aws. prefix (aws.eventSource, aws.userIdentity.*, ...)
    or they match NOTHING. These rules previously OMITTED the prefix and so
    never fired (confirmed: cloudtrail-group alert count was 0 while the
    aws group had 192k+ docs). The prefix has now been added throughout.

  CI role suppression (100302, 100303, 100305):
    Changes via the GitHubActionsDeployRole assumed-role session are expected
    IaC operations and must NOT alert. For assumed-role callers the decoder
    populates aws.userIdentity.sessionContext.sessionIssuer.arn (the role ARN);
    the negate field matches the role name there. If the role is renamed,
    update the pcre2 pattern.

  Deferred / blocked detections (verified 2026-06-02 — do NOT re-add blindly):
    - SSO console login (was rule 100304, REMOVED): IAM Identity Center auth
      events are logged in the Identity Center MANAGEMENT account 480875379870,
      not in this member account. This trail only sees read-only sso.amazonaws.com
      portal calls (GetSSOStatus, ListInstances). Real SSO-login detection needs
      a rule + log source in the management account. Re-add only with that source.
    - S3 object-access exfil (no ID assigned, NOT added): GetObject is a CloudTrail
      DATA event. Both trails (bc-ctrl-trail + Control Tower baseline) log
      management events only (DataResources: []). Enabling S3 data events is a
      paid, per-event feature — gate behind a cost decision before adding.

  Threat rules 100306-100312 (added 2026-06-02): defense-evasion, persistence,
  impact, and credential/compute-abuse detections. Negate-lists were derived
  from the ACTUAL legitimate callers observed in CloudTrail (CI role, the ESO
  IRSA role, the wazuh/misp EC2 roles, and AWS service-linked roles), so a
  sensitive action by anything else is high-fidelity in this SSO-only,
  IaC-driven account. Human (SSO-admin) actions are intentionally NOT negated
  on 100311/100312 — a person reading a secret or launching an instance by hand
  is exactly what we want SOAR to see.
-->
<group name="bc-aws,cloudtrail,">

  <!-- ============================================================
       100300 — Console login without MFA (IAM user path)
       MITRE: T1078 (Valid Accounts)  |  Level 12: high, paged.

       COVERAGE NOTE: Fires only for IAM-user console logins
       (aws.eventSource signin.amazonaws.com, MFAUsed present). SSO logins
       are NOT covered here — see the "Deferred" note in the file header.
  ============================================================ -->
  <rule id="100300" level="12">
    <decoded_as>json</decoded_as>
    <field name="aws.eventSource">signin.amazonaws.com</field>
    <field name="aws.eventName">ConsoleLogin</field>
    <field name="aws.responseElements.ConsoleLogin">Success</field>
    <field name="aws.additionalEventData.MFAUsed">No</field>
    <description>AWS Console login without MFA — $(aws.userIdentity.userName) from $(aws.sourceIPAddress)</description>
    <mitre>
      <id>T1078</id>
    </mitre>
    <group>authentication,pci_dss_8.3,gdpr_IV_35.7.d,</group>
  </rule>

  <!-- ============================================================
       100301 — Root account used (any console sign-in event)
       MITRE: T1078.004 (Cloud Accounts)  |  Level 15: critical.
  ============================================================ -->
  <rule id="100301" level="15">
    <decoded_as>json</decoded_as>
    <field name="aws.userIdentity.type">Root</field>
    <field name="aws.eventType">AwsConsoleSignIn</field>
    <description>AWS root account used — CRITICAL — from $(aws.sourceIPAddress)</description>
    <mitre>
      <id>T1078.004</id>
    </mitre>
    <group>authentication,pci_dss_10.2.2,gdpr_IV_35.7.d,</group>
  </rule>

  <!-- ============================================================
       100302 — Security Group modified (not by CI pipeline)
       MITRE: T1562.007 (Disable or Modify Cloud Firewall)
       Level 8: medium. Suppressed for GitHubActionsDeployRole (IaC expected).
  ============================================================ -->
  <rule id="100302" level="8">
    <decoded_as>json</decoded_as>
    <field name="aws.eventSource">ec2.amazonaws.com</field>
    <field name="aws.eventName" type="pcre2">.*SecurityGroup.*</field>
    <field name="aws.userIdentity.sessionContext.sessionIssuer.arn" negate="yes" type="pcre2">GitHubActionsDeployRole</field>
    <description>AWS Security Group modified — $(aws.eventName) by $(aws.userIdentity.userName)</description>
    <mitre>
      <id>T1562.007</id>
    </mitre>
    <group>configuration_changed,pci_dss_1.1.1,</group>
  </rule>

  <!-- ============================================================
       100303 — IAM role or policy modified (not by CI pipeline)
       MITRE: T1098 (Account Manipulation)
       Level 10: high. Suppressed for GitHubActionsDeployRole (IaC expected).
  ============================================================ -->
  <rule id="100303" level="10">
    <decoded_as>json</decoded_as>
    <field name="aws.eventSource">iam.amazonaws.com</field>
    <field name="aws.eventName" type="pcre2">.*(Role|Policy).*</field>
    <field name="aws.userIdentity.sessionContext.sessionIssuer.arn" negate="yes" type="pcre2">GitHubActionsDeployRole</field>
    <description>AWS IAM role/policy modified — $(aws.eventName) by $(aws.userIdentity.userName)</description>
    <mitre>
      <id>T1098</id>
    </mitre>
    <group>configuration_changed,pci_dss_8.1,</group>
  </rule>

  <!-- (100304 intentionally unused — SSO login detection removed; see header) -->

  <!-- ============================================================
       100305 — Unexpected SSM session/command on bc-ctrl EC2
       MITRE: T1552.005 (Unsecured Credentials: Cloud Instance Metadata API)
       Level 12: high. An attacker with ssm:StartSession/SendCommand on
       wazuh-ctrl or misp-ctrl can read the instance profile credentials from
       IMDS. SOAR should triage the session and rotate the profile if unexpected.

       Field paths verified 2026-06-02 against a live SendCommand event:
         aws.eventSource = ssm.amazonaws.com
         aws.eventName   = SendCommand | StartSession
         aws.requestParameters.instanceIds[] (SendCommand) / .target (StartSession)

       Suppression: the legitimate callers are the CI role AND the SSO admin
       role (AWSReservedSSO_AdministratorAccess_*) — both are negated. NOTE:
       negating the SSO admin role means a compromised admin session will NOT
       fire this rule; drop "AWSReservedSSO_AdministratorAccess" from the pcre2
       below to turn this into full privileged-SSM-access monitoring (noisier,
       but catches insider/credential-theft use of the admin role).
  ============================================================ -->
  <rule id="100305" level="12">
    <decoded_as>json</decoded_as>
    <field name="aws.eventSource">ssm.amazonaws.com</field>
    <field name="aws.eventName" type="pcre2">^(StartSession|SendCommand)$</field>
    <field name="aws.userIdentity.sessionContext.sessionIssuer.arn" negate="yes" type="pcre2">GitHubActionsDeployRole|AWSReservedSSO_AdministratorAccess</field>
    <description>Unexpected SSM session/command — $(aws.eventName) by $(aws.userIdentity.arn)</description>
    <mitre>
      <id>T1552.005</id>
    </mitre>
    <group>credential_access,ssm,</group>
  </rule>

  <!-- ============================================================
       100306 — CloudTrail / logging tampering
       MITRE: T1562.008 (Disable or Modify Cloud Logs)  |  Level 13
       Blinding the SIEM is a classic first move. Negate CI (it manages the
       trail config via UpdateTrail/PutEventSelectors on apply).
  ============================================================ -->
  <rule id="100306" level="13">
    <decoded_as>json</decoded_as>
    <field name="aws.eventSource">cloudtrail.amazonaws.com</field>
    <field name="aws.eventName" type="pcre2">^(StopLogging|DeleteTrail|UpdateTrail|PutEventSelectors)$</field>
    <field name="aws.userIdentity.sessionContext.sessionIssuer.arn" negate="yes" type="pcre2">GitHubActionsDeployRole</field>
    <description>CloudTrail logging tampered — $(aws.eventName) by $(aws.userIdentity.arn)</description>
    <mitre>
      <id>T1562.008</id>
    </mitre>
    <group>defense_evasion,cloudtrail_tampering,</group>
  </rule>

  <!-- ============================================================
       100307 — Security detection plane disabled
       MITRE: T1562.001 (Disable or Modify Tools)  |  Level 13
       GuardDuty / AWS Config / Security Hub teardown. Matched on eventName
       (eventSource varies by service). Negate CI (manages Config recorder).
  ============================================================ -->
  <rule id="100307" level="13">
    <decoded_as>json</decoded_as>
    <field name="aws.eventName" type="pcre2">^(DeleteDetector|DisableOrganizationAdminAccount|StopMonitoringMembers|DeleteConfigurationRecorder|StopConfigurationRecorder|DeleteDeliveryChannel|DisableSecurityHub|BatchDisableStandards)$</field>
    <field name="aws.userIdentity.sessionContext.sessionIssuer.arn" negate="yes" type="pcre2">GitHubActionsDeployRole</field>
    <description>Security detection plane disabled — $(aws.eventName) by $(aws.userIdentity.arn)</description>
    <mitre>
      <id>T1562.001</id>
    </mitre>
    <group>defense_evasion,detection_disabled,</group>
  </rule>

  <!-- ============================================================
       100308 — KMS key disabled or scheduled for deletion
       MITRE: T1485 (Data Destruction)  |  Level 14
       KMS is central to the snapshot/encryption story. No negate — even a
       pipeline-driven key deletion is rare and destructive enough to surface.
  ============================================================ -->
  <rule id="100308" level="14">
    <decoded_as>json</decoded_as>
    <field name="aws.eventSource">kms.amazonaws.com</field>
    <field name="aws.eventName" type="pcre2">^(ScheduleKeyDeletion|DisableKey)$</field>
    <description>KMS key disabled / scheduled for deletion — $(aws.requestParameters.keyId) by $(aws.userIdentity.arn)</description>
    <mitre>
      <id>T1485</id>
    </mitre>
    <group>impact,kms,data_destruction,</group>
  </rule>

  <!-- ============================================================
       100309 — IAM access key created
       MITRE: T1098 (Account Manipulation)  |  Level 12
       The account is SSO-only with zero IAM users — ANY long-lived access key
       is anomalous persistence. No negate (CI does not create keys either).
  ============================================================ -->
  <rule id="100309" level="12">
    <decoded_as>json</decoded_as>
    <field name="aws.eventSource">iam.amazonaws.com</field>
    <field name="aws.eventName">CreateAccessKey</field>
    <description>IAM access key created (account is SSO-only — investigate) — for user $(aws.requestParameters.userName) by $(aws.userIdentity.arn)</description>
    <mitre>
      <id>T1098</id>
    </mitre>
    <group>persistence,iam,credential_creation,</group>
  </rule>

  <!-- ============================================================
       100310 — IAM user or login profile created
       MITRE: T1136.001 (Create Account: Local Account)  |  Level 12
       Establishing a non-SSO foothold. No negate.
  ============================================================ -->
  <rule id="100310" level="12">
    <decoded_as>json</decoded_as>
    <field name="aws.eventSource">iam.amazonaws.com</field>
    <field name="aws.eventName" type="pcre2">^(CreateUser|CreateLoginProfile)$</field>
    <description>IAM user/login profile created (account is SSO-only) — $(aws.eventName) target $(aws.requestParameters.userName) by $(aws.userIdentity.arn)</description>
    <mitre>
      <id>T1136.001</id>
    </mitre>
    <group>persistence,iam,account_creation,</group>
  </rule>

  <!-- ============================================================
       100311 — Secrets Manager value read by unexpected principal
       MITRE: T1552 (Unsecured Credentials)  |  Level 12
       Legit readers (verified via CloudTrail 2026-06-02): the ESO IRSA role,
       the CI role, and the wazuh/misp EC2 roles. A GetSecretValue from anyone
       else — including a human SSO-admin session — is surfaced for SOAR triage.
  ============================================================ -->
  <rule id="100311" level="12">
    <decoded_as>json</decoded_as>
    <field name="aws.eventSource">secretsmanager.amazonaws.com</field>
    <field name="aws.eventName">GetSecretValue</field>
    <field name="aws.userIdentity.sessionContext.sessionIssuer.arn" negate="yes" type="pcre2">bc-uatms-prd-external-secrets|GitHubActionsDeployRole|wazuh-ec2-role|misp-ec2-role</field>
    <description>Secrets Manager value read by unexpected principal — $(aws.requestParameters.secretId) by $(aws.userIdentity.arn)</description>
    <mitre>
      <id>T1552</id>
    </mitre>
    <group>credential_access,secretsmanager,</group>
  </rule>

  <!-- ============================================================
       100312 — EC2 instance launched outside the pipeline
       MITRE: T1496 (Resource Hijacking)  |  Level 12
       Legit launchers (verified): CI role + AWS service-linked roles for EKS
       node groups and Auto Scaling. Human SSO-admin launches are intentionally
       NOT negated — that is exactly the rogue-box case (e.g. the undocumented
       cheap-test-ubuntu-soar-test instance) we want to catch.
  ============================================================ -->
  <rule id="100312" level="12">
    <decoded_as>json</decoded_as>
    <field name="aws.eventSource">ec2.amazonaws.com</field>
    <field name="aws.eventName">RunInstances</field>
    <field name="aws.userIdentity.sessionContext.sessionIssuer.arn" negate="yes" type="pcre2">GitHubActionsDeployRole|AWSServiceRoleForAmazonEKSNodegroup|AWSServiceRoleForAutoScaling</field>
    <description>EC2 instance launched outside the pipeline — by $(aws.userIdentity.arn)</description>
    <mitre>
      <id>T1496</id>
    </mitre>
    <group>execution,ec2,rogue_compute,</group>
  </rule>

</group>
